{"bill":{"bill_id":1645787,"change_hash":"a543108cae9c866412c757cba52bddff","session_id":2021,"session":{"session_id":2021,"state_id":14,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IN\/bill\/SB0037\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/iga.in.gov\/legislative\/2023\/bills\/senate\/37\/","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-01-25","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-09","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-09","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-17","event":10},{"date":"2023-01-25","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-07","event":9}],"state":"IN","state_id":14,"bill_number":"SB0037","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":38,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":37,"title":"Food and beverage taxes.","description":"Food and beverage taxes. Requires each local unit that imposes a food and beverage tax to annually report information concerning distributions and expenditures of amounts received from the food and beverage tax. Provides that food and beverage taxes currently authorized under IC 6-9 and that do not otherwise contain an expiration date (other than the stadium and convention building authority food and beverage tax and the historic hotels food and beverage tax) shall expire on the later of: (1) January 1, 2045; or (2) the date on which all bonds or lease agreements outstanding on May 7, 2023, are completely paid. Requires each local unit that imposes a food and beverage tax that is subject to the expiration provision to provide to the department of local government finance (department) a list of each bond or lease agreement outstanding on May 7, 2023, and the date on which each will be completely paid. Requires the department to publish the information on the gateway website. Declares the intention of the general assembly to only authorize local units to impose new food and beverage taxes based on specified criteria.","pending_committee_id":1307,"committee":{"committee_id":1307,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"name":"Ways and Means"},"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-09","committee_id":1335,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"name":"Tax and Fiscal Policy"},{"date":"2023-02-07","committee_id":1307,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"name":"Ways and Means"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-09","action":"Authored by Senator Gaskill","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-09","action":"First reading: referred to Committee on Tax and Fiscal Policy","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Senator Holdman added as second author","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-17","action":"Committee report: amend do pass, adopted","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-23","action":"Amendment #1 (Holdman) prevailed; voice vote","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-23","action":"Second reading: amended, ordered engrossed","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Third reading: passed; Roll Call 15: yeas 50, nays 0","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"House sponsor: Representative Prescott","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Cosponsor: Representative Goodrich","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Senator Rogers added as third author","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Senator Messmer added as coauthor","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Senator Niezgodski added as coauthor","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Referred to the House","chamber":"S","chamber_id":38,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-07","action":"First reading: referred to Committee on Ways and Means","chamber":"H","chamber_id"